          <li class=3D"none text-body">
            <h4 class=3D"t-question active">
              <span class=3D"q-txt">What is a Handicap Index?</span>
              <span class=3D"icon">
                <svg width=3D"22" height=3D"22" viewBox=3D"0 0 22 22" fill=
=3D"none" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path id=3D"v-line" d=3D"M1 11H21" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                  <path id=3D"h-line" d=3D"M11 21V1" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </h4>
            <div class=3D"t-answer active">
              <p><strong>Definition: </strong>A Handicap Index reflects you=
r <strong>potential playing ability</strong>, calculated from the best 8 of=
 your last 20 score differentials, adjusted for course rating, slope, and p=
laying conditions. It levels the playing field between golfers of different=
 skill levels.</p>
<p>Not all golfers are created equal, but with the golf handicap system, th=
ey can all compete with one another on an equal basis. For example, Tom=E2=
=80=99s average score is 80 and Meaghan=E2=80=99s average score is 95. With=
 the handicap system, Tom =E2=80=98gives=E2=80=99 Meaghan a calculated numb=
er of strokes to level the playing field such that either of them has the s=
ame chance to win.</p>
<p><strong>To put it simply, handicaps are equalizers.</strong></p>
<p>Want a real (golf) world example? Read to learn what a golf handicap is!=
</p>
<p><strong><!--HubSpot Call-to-Action Code --><span class=3D"hs-cta-wrapper=
