         =20
          <li class=3D"none text-body">
            <h4 class=3D"t-question ">
              <span class=3D"q-txt">How do I get a Handicap Index?</span>
              <span class=3D"icon">
                <svg width=3D"22" height=3D"22" viewBox=3D"0 0 22 22" fill=
=3D"none" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path id=3D"v-line" d=3D"M1 11H21" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                  <path id=3D"h-line" d=3D"M11 21V1" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </h4>
            <div class=3D"t-answer ">
              <p>In the U.S., each state has one or more Allied Golf Associ=
ations (AGA=E2=80=99s) which are the authorized organizations for issuing a=
nd maintaining official WHS (World Handicap System) Handicaps. In Northern =
California, this is the NCGA.</p>
<h5>Here are the basic 4 steps to get a Handicap Index:</h5>
<h6>Step 1:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://ncga.org/join?hsLang=3Den" rel=3D"noope=
ner">Join a Golf Club</a></h6>
<p>To join the NCGA and get a Handicap Index, you must join a club. The fas=
test and easiest way to join is to <a href=3D"https://ncga.org/join?hsLang=
=3Den" rel=3D"noopener">Join NCGA direct via eClub</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<h6>Step 2: <a href=3D"https://blog.ncga.org/how-to-get-a-golf-handicap?hsL=
ang=3Den#ghin" rel=3D"noopener">Get your GHIN Number</a></h6>
<p>Once you join a club and get your GHIN number (Golf Handicap Information=
 Network) which is a unique-to-you, numerical number that follows you aroun=
d similar to a SSN to track your scoring history.&nbsp;</p>
<h6>Step 3: <a href=3D"https://blog.ncga.org/how-to-get-a-golf-handicap?hsL=
ang=3Den#post" rel=3D"noopener">Post a minimum of 54 holes</a></h6>
<p>Using the GHIN app, you will then post a minimum of 54 holes<strong> </s=
trong>(can be a mix of 18-hole scores and 9-hole scores) in the WHS system =
and your Handicap Index will be calculated.</p>
<h6>Step 4: <a href=3D"https://blog.ncga.org/how-to-get-a-golf-handicap?hsL=
ang=3Den#maintain" rel=3D"noopener">Wait... a day!</a></h6>
<p>After you post the 54 holes, the system will automatically update on a d=
aily basis with your calculated Handicap Index.</p>
<p>You will also receive Handicap Index Revisions via email on the 1st and =
15th of every month.</p>
<p>Until your Handicap Index is calculated, you will see it listed as =E2=
=80=98NH=E2=80=99 which stands for No Handicap.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Want all the details on exactly how to get a golf handicap?</p>
