         =20
          <li class=3D"none text-body">
            <h4 class=3D"t-question ">
              <span class=3D"q-txt">What is a Net Score?</span>
              <span class=3D"icon">
                <svg width=3D"22" height=3D"22" viewBox=3D"0 0 22 22" fill=
=3D"none" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path id=3D"v-line" d=3D"M1 11H21" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                  <path id=3D"h-line" d=3D"M11 21V1" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </h4>
            <div class=3D"t-answer ">
              <p>When you play a round of golf, the total number of strokes=
 you take is your =E2=80=98gross score=E2=80=99. The =E2=80=98net score=E2=
=80=99 is determined by subtracting the Course Handicap from the gross scor=
e.</p>
<p>Following the above example: you play a round and your gross score is 89=
, subtract your course handicap 18, your net score is 71. That is a net par=
 at Poppy Hills Golf Course!</p>
            </div>
          </li>
         =20
          <li class=3D"none text-body">
            <h4 class=3D"t-question ">
              <span class=3D"q-txt">What is Maximum Hole Score?</span>
              <span class=3D"icon">
                <svg width=3D"22" height=3D"22" viewBox=3D"0 0 22 22" fill=
=3D"none" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path id=3D"v-line" d=3D"M1 11H21" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                  <path id=3D"h-line" d=3D"M11 21V1" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </h4>
            <div class=3D"t-answer ">
              <h5>What is the maximum # of strokes I would post on a hole?<=
/h5>
<p>Ever had a bad hole, like getting a 10 on a par 4? For a player with an =
established Handicap Index, for score posting purposes only, the <a href=3D=
"https://support.ncga.org/knowledge/maximum-hole-score?hsLang=3Den" rel=3D"=
noopener">Maximum Hole Score</a> will be a <strong>net double bogey</strong=
>. That is a gross double bogey, plus any handicap strokes (=E2=80=98pops=
=E2=80=99) the golfer is entitled to on that hole based upon the ranking of=
 the stroke holes.</p>
<p>For example, if you have a 25 handicap, the max hole score will be a gro=
ss quadruple bogey on the 7 hardest holes and a gross triple bogey for the =
remaining 11 holes. There is now a score posting feature for =E2=80=98hole-=
by-hole=E2=80=99 scoring in the GHIN app. If you use this, the system will =
do the calculations for you. (Prior to 2020, there was a similar concept ca=
lled ESC which is no longer used.)</p>
<p>For a player submitting their <em>first scores to obtain an initial Hand=
icap Index</em>, the maximum score for each hole played is limited to <stro=
ng>par + 5 strokes</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
         =20
          <li class=3D"none text-body">
            <h4 class=3D"t-question ">
              <span class=3D"q-txt">How to =E2=80=98give and get strokes=E2=
=80=99?</span>
              <span class=3D"icon">
                <svg width=3D"22" height=3D"22" viewBox=3D"0 0 22 22" fill=
=3D"none" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path id=3D"v-line" d=3D"M1 11H21" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                  <path id=3D"h-line" d=3D"M11 21V1" stroke=3D"#0055A5" str=
oke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"round" stroke-linejoin=3D"round"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </h4>
            <div class=3D"t-answer ">
              <h5>How do players with different handicaps =E2=80=98give and=
 get strokes=E2=80=99?</h5>
<p>This is the true beauty of the handicap system. If your buddy or competi=
tor has a course handicap of 14, and you have a course handicap of 21, they=
 have to =E2=80=98give=E2=80=99 you 7 strokes, sometimes called =E2=80=98po=
ps=E2=80=99. If they beat you by 7 strokes, you tie; if they beat you by on=
ly 6 strokes, you win! This is the handicap at work!</p>
<p>The example below shows how strokes are applied in the GHIN App.</p>
<p>Bryan is a 2.9 handicap and Aimee is a 16.4 handicap. If they were to co=
mpete in match play at Poppy Hills Golf Course, they would need to apply th=
e scoring differential for 18-holes as shown below.</p>
<p>Bryan would have to "give" Aimee 12 strokes since she is playing the Ora=
nge tees and Bryan the Black tees. This allows Aimee to compete fairly with=
 Bryan during their friendly competitions.</p>
<p><img src=3D"https://ncga.org/hs-fs/hubfs/Aimee%20and%20Bryan%20Poppy%20H=
ills%20Match%20Play-landscape.png?width=3D900&amp;height=3D457&amp;name=3DA=
imee%20and%20Bryan%20Poppy%20Hills%20Match%20Play-landscape.png" width=3D"9=
00" height=3D"457" loading=3D"lazy" alt=3D"Aimee and Bryan Poppy Hills Matc=
h Play-landscape" style=3D"height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 900px; mar=
gin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;"></p>
<p>Want to learn how to use the <span>GHIN Mobile App's Handicap Calculator=
 to Play with Friends? Check out the article below!</span></p>
